I’ve read a lot about banks and their employees in Morocco. Today, I opened an account at this bank, and I was pleasantly surprised by the service. I was assisted by a friendly employee named Khadija, who was very helpful and professional.

To open an account, you need a rental agreement for an apartment/house or a property ownership document, and a passport (for foreigners). The account can be opened in both dirhams and euros. I can receive funds from abroad in euros and then convert them to dirhams. While I cannot deposit dirhams in cash into my account, it is possible to receive dirhams via bank transfer from a Moroccan account.

Overall, the experience was very positive, especially due to Khadija’s professionalism. I highly recommend this bank if you are looking for a reliable financial institution in Morocco.

I immediately expressed my dissatisfaction to the agent in question, making it clear to her that her attitude was inappropriate and that she needed to review the way she treated customers, regardless of their profile.

I therefore urge you to take appropriate measures to remedy this situation. It is essential that you take disciplinary action and provide additional training to this agent to instill the skills necessary to treat customers in a respectful and professional manner.
